  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6819.45 sitting just below the massive 6825 gamma wall (+5.6B) in PIN regime, dealers are likely selling into this move higher as they hedge their long gamma positions. The recent wall_break event combined with the -3.7% short-term momentum suggests we're seeing dealer resistance kick in near these key levels. Given the strong positive gamma cluster between 6810-6825 (13.6B combined), expect heavy two-way flow and mean reversion pressure with 6825 acting as a magnet and potential ceiling.\n\nKey levels: 6825 resistance (dealers sell), 6797 GEX flip for regime change, and 6700 support zone where dealers would aggressively buy dips.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action with upside capped near 6825 as dealers fight the rally.",
